===Noun===
{{en-noun|maxima|s}}

# The [[high|highest]] [[limit]].
#* P. Colquhoun
#*: Good legislation is the art of conducting a nation to the '''maximum''' of happiness, and the minimum of misery.
# {{label|en|mathematics}} The [[great]]est [[value]] of a [[set]] or other mathematical structure, especially the [[global maximum]] or a [[local maximum]] of a [[function]].
# {{label|en|analysis}} An [[upper bound]] of a set which is also an element of that set.
# {{label|en|statistics}} The largest value of a [[batch]] or [[sample]] or the upper bound of a [[probability distribution]].
# {{label|en|colloquial|snooker}} A 147 break; the highest possible break.
# {{label|en|colloquial|darts}} A [[score]] of [[180]] with three darts.
# {{label|en|colloquial|cricket}} A scoring shot for 6 runs.

